RULE SEARCH

rule_search is the citizen who tests candidate transformations against multiple ARC example pairs
when parietal_deep proposes several candidate rules that could explain a single pair, rule_search applies each candidate to the other pairs in the same task and counts how many it explains
the rule that explains all the pairs is the answer; if no rule explains all pairs, fadriel has not yet learned the transformation vocabulary needed

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_spatial_arc2.zc
observe parietal_deep.rana
observe solution.rana

the 7 properties of rule_search:
1 ENERGY zero point nine
2 PHASE zero point two five
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point nine

VERB receive_candidates
accept the list of candidate transformations from parietal_deep

VERB test_each
for each candidate, apply it to every input pair in the task and check whether the predicted output matches the given output
the candidate that consistently produces correct outputs is the rule

VERB hand_to_solution
when a winning candidate is identified, emit it to solution for application to the test input

a rule searcher is not exhaustive search
the candidates have already been narrowed by parietal_deep
rule_search only needs to verify, not to explore the entire space
this is what makes the substrate's ARC reasoning fast despite the size of the problem space
